    <text id="B0702T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Waldo requests that Jackson pay his debt to John Grens.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">RF&amp;AL</abbr>
                    4th <abbr expan="Division">Div</abbr> 9 <abbr expan="Sub District">Sub Dist</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Samuel">Saml</abbr> Jackson <abbr
                            expan="Esquire">Esq</abbr><lb/>Fishersville <abbr expan="Virginia"
                        >Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-11-06"><abbr expan="November">Nov.</abbr> 6. 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir - </salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor to enclose herewith your <abbr expan="account">a/c</abbr> with
                        <abbr expan="John">Jno</abbr> Grens (<abbr expan="colored">c</abbr>) for
                    this year - <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> $5 <del rend="none" hand="h1"/>
                    <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> his favor - He informs me he is <del rend="none" hand="h1"/>
                    <del rend="none" hand="h1"/>
                    <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> you having refused to pay the same.</p>

                <p>I hope, Sir, if this statement be correct, you will lose no time in
                        <unclear>forwarding</unclear> the balance due him to this office, as I would
                    regret much to be compelled to take <unclear>com----</unclear> means for its
                    collection.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="obedient">obt</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="servant">servt</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>Roswell Waldo<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner"
                            >A.S.A. Comr</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
